text: Expression and Activity of <extra_id_0> MMP9 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> Were Greatly Enhanced in Nrf2 Knockout Astrocytes after Scratch Injury
<extra_id_0> MMP9 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> is an important gelatinase to induce or aggravate the inflammation process .

In the present study , we elevated the mRNA , protein levels , and activity of <extra_id_0> MMP9 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> in astrocytes at 24 h after scratch injury by RT-PCR , western blot , and gelatine zymography .
Expression of <extra_id_0> MMP9 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> was elevated after scratch injury in WT and KO astrocytes as compared with their sham counterparts .

The mRNA level of <extra_id_0> MMP9 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> was higher in group KO TBI than in group WT TBI ( 1.36 +/- 0.090 versus 1.01 +/- 0.068 , P < 0.01 ) ( Figures 3 ( a ) and 3 ( e ) ) .

Significant difference was also discovered in <extra_id_0> MMP9 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> protein level by western blot , as 1.44 +/- 0.076 for group KO TBI and 1.13 +/- 0.048 for group WT TBI ( P < 0.01 ) ( Figure 5 ) .

Gelatine zymography revealed higher <extra_id_0> MMP9 <extra_id_2> Protein <extra_id_1> activity in group KO TBI than that in group WT TBI too ( 101.76 +/- 6.343 versus 76.32 +/- 3.388 , P < 0.01 ) ( Figure 6 ) .
